The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Madurai, Dec. 7 (PTI): A mobile phone that started ringing from inside a donation box created panic among devotees in the Madapuram temple in Sivaganga district yesterday, police said.           
	Tight security arrangements had been made at the temple. The owner of the phone is being traced. It was not known if the phone had fallen accidentally into the box.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi Consumer Commission has awarded Rs 5,000 to a man who found dead mosquitoes in a Pepsi bottle. The company had appealed against a district forums award of Rs 10,000 to the customer Pankaj Dua.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Tihar jail officials are segregating under-trials according to the courts in which they are to appear in a bid to streamline its administrative functioning. Under-trials were being lodged on an as they come basis which caused overcrowding in some wards.                  
	 Farukhabad (PTI): Over 11,000 prisoners have gone on a hunger strike at Fatehgarh central jail in Uttar Pradesh, officials said. The prisoners have alleged they were not given adequate food for the past few weeks and their relatives and friends had to bribe staff to meet them.                  
	 Bahraich (PTI): A fast track court in Bahraich, Uttar Pradesh, has jailed a man for 10 years for raping a minor girl and awarded a seven-year term to his accomplice. Kaushal and Manju were accused of raping the girl in their village on March 25, 2005.                  
	 Palakkad (PTI): Six members of a family, including an infant, were killed on Sunday when the car in which they were travelling collided with a lorry at Kanjikode junction on the national highway near Palakkad in Kerala. The victims were on their way to the Guruvayur temple.                                                                                                                         
